{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180424767,"sessionID":"ses_361d75adcffeCdUmEUSP3DCUv6","part":{"id":"prt_c9e2ef9bd001Fy06SQPPIhselU","sessionID":"ses_361d75adcffeCdUmEUSP3DCUv6","messageID":"msg_c9e2ef63a001nUMgph747DGyfg","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_011SDpCUrK6oWtKV5DV5tKSn","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/run-state.md","content":"# Run State\n\n> Persists per-run artifacts: timestamped run directory, live `session.json`,\n> JSONL event log, and per-iteration transcripts.\n\n**Source:** `src/run-state.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe run-state module creates and maintains the file-based record of a single\nengine run. It is the write side of the run artifact system; `src/run-status.ts`\nis the corresponding read side. A `RunTracker` instance is created at the\nstart of each engine run and holds the run directory open for the duration,\nflushing state after every event and appending event records to an append-only\nJSONL log.\n\n## Triggers\n\n- `startRunTracker(projectDir, description, maxIterations)` — called by the\n  Engine at the beginning of every run. (`src/engine.ts`)\n- `RunTracker.recordEvent(event)` — called by the Engine each time an\n  `EngineEvent` is emitted.\n- `RunTracker.writeIterationTranscript(iteration, label, rawOutput?, displayOutput?)` —\n  called by the Engine after each iteration completes.\n- `RunTracker.finalize(status)` — called by the Engine in its `finally`\n  block when the run ends.\n\n## Inputs\n\n| Name | Type | Source | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `projectDir` | `string` | Engine | Absolute path to the project root |\n| `description` | `string` | phase `setup` return | Human-readable description of the run |\n| `maxIterations` | `number` | phase `setup` return | Upper bound on iterations for this run |\n| `event` | `EngineEvent` | Engine event emitter | Typed engine lifecycle event to record |\n| `iteration` | `number` | Engine | Iteration index (1-based) |\n| `label` | `string` | Engine | Short label identifying the iteration (e.g., bead ID or title) |\n| `rawOutput` | `string \\| undefined` | `src/output-parser.ts` | Raw JSON event log from the session |\n| `displayOutput` | `string \\| undefined` | `src/output-parser.ts` | Human-readable session transcript |\n| `status` | `string` | Engine | Final run status string written to `session.json` |\n\n## Outputs\n\n| Name | Type | Destination | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `startRunTracker` return | `RunTracker` | Engine | Handle with `runId`, `runDir`, and the four tracker methods |\n\n## Side Effects\n\n- Creates `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/` directory and `iterations/`\n  subdirectory on construction.\n- Writes `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/session.json` (full JSON state) after\n  every `recordEvent` call and after `finalize`.\n- Writes `.super-ralph/session.json` (global latest-run pointer) after\n  every `recordEvent` call and after `finalize`.\n- Appends one JSON line to `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/events.jsonl` for\n  each `recordEvent` call.\n- Writes `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/iterations/<NNN>-<label>.log` for each\n  `writeIterationTranscript` call.\n\n## Failure Modes\n\n| Condition | Behavior | Recovery |\n|---|---|---|\n| File system write fails | Exception propagates from the synchronous `fs.writeFileSync` call | Engine's `finally` block may not complete cleanly; artifacts are partially written |\n| `startRunTracker` called when `.super-ralph/` does not exist | `fs.mkdirSync` creates the full path (recursive) | No error; directories are created on demand |\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `src/events.ts` | internal | `EngineEvent` type used in `recordEvent` parameter |\n| `fs` | node | All file creation, writing, and directory operations |\n| `path` | node | Constructs paths within the run directory |\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- The run ID format (`\"<timestamp>-<random6chars>\"`) uses a timestamp and\n  random suffix. The clock source and entropy source for the random component\n  are not documented in source.\n- Whether `writeIterationTranscript` writes `rawOutput`, `displayOutput`,\n  or both to the same file or separate files is not explicitly stated in\n  observable source comments.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":"spec/modules/infrastructure/run-state.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/beads.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/decompose.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":12,"character":16},"end":{"line":12,"character":22}},"message":"'config' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":80,"character":31},"end":{"line":80,"character":40}},"message":"'iteration' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"}],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/config.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":89,"character":2},"end":{"line":89,"character":11}},"message":"'beadTitle' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"}],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/engine.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/events.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/forward.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":12,"character":16},"end":{"line":12,"character":22}},"message":"'config' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":12,"character":24},"end":{"line":12,"character":30}},"message":"'dryRun' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":21,"character":32},"end":{"line":21,"character":41}},"message":"'iteration' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"},{"range":{"start":{"line":78,"character":31},"end":{"line":78,"character":40}},"message":"'iteration' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"}],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/index.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/init.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/interactive.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/opencode.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/output-parser.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/progress.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/reverse.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":219,"character":31},"end":{"line":219,"character":40}},"message":"'iteration' is declared but its value is never read.","severity":4,"code":6133,"source":"typescript"}],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/run-state.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/run-status.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/skills.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/template.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/timeout.ts":[],"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/src/types.ts":[]},"filepath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/run-state.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772180424733,"end":1772180424765}}}}
