{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180621400,"sessionID":"ses_361d75adcffeCdUmEUSP3DCUv6","part":{"id":"prt_c9e324330001nqcf7ecs1FBDJl","sessionID":"ses_361d75adcffeCdUmEUSP3DCUv6","messageID":"msg_c9e322a7b001u1QzGcR53I6ckD","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_013TXpubuTNjdkdPUbm4jx9E","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/config.md","offset":1,"limit":10},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/config.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Config\n2: \n3: > Loads and merges `.super-ralph/config.toml` with hard-coded defaults, and\n4: > resolves the AI model to use for a given bead.\n5: \n6: **Source:** `src/config.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n7: \n8: ## Purpose\n9: \n10: The config module provides the single entry point for reading project-level\n\n(Showing lines 1-10 of 74. Use offset=11 to continue.)\n</content>","title":"spec/modules/infrastructure/config.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Config\n\n> Loads and merges `.super-ralph/config.toml` with hard-coded defaults, and\n> resolves the AI model to use for a given bead.\n\n**Source:** `src/config.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe config module provides the single entry point for reading project-level","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772180621396,"end":1772180621399}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180622122,"sessionID":"ses_361d75adcffeCdUmEUSP3DCUv6","part":{"id":"prt_c9e324855001t75y1l0010NFyX","sessionID":"ses_361d75adcffeCdUmEUSP3DCUv6","messageID":"msg_c9e322a7b001u1QzGcR53I6ckD","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01MBy9tdq5jwScYANJCDYzEa","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/init.md","offset":1,"limit":65},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/init.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Init\n2: \n3: > Scaffolds a new project: creates `.super-ralph/`, copies templates, writes\n4: > `config.toml`, installs the OpenCode plugin, and runs `br init`.\n5: \n6: **Source:** `src/init.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n7: \n8: ## Purpose\n9: \n10: The init module performs one-time project setup for `super-ralph`. It is\n11: idempotent: running it more than once will skip files that already exist\n12: rather than overwriting them. The module wires together the three external\n13: dependencies a project needs: the `.super-ralph/` configuration directory,\n14: the OpenCode plugin that provides the `task_complete` tool, and the `.beads/`\n15: workspace.\n16: \n17: ## Triggers\n18: \n19: - `runInit(projectDir)` — called by `src/index.ts` when the user runs\n20:   `super-ralph init`. (`src/index.ts:cmdInit`)\n21: \n22: ## Inputs\n23: \n24: | Name | Type | Source | Description |\n25: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n26: | `projectDir` | `string` | CLI caller | Absolute path to the project root where the project is scaffolded |\n27: \n28: ## Outputs\n29: \n30: _Not applicable for this module._ `runInit` returns `Promise<void>` and\n31: communicates results only through console output and side effects.\n32: \n33: ## Side Effects\n34: \n35: All side effects are idempotent (skip if the target already exists):\n36: \n37: 1. Creates `.super-ralph/` directory.\n38: 2. Copies `AGENTS.md`, `forward.hbs`, `decompose.hbs`, `reverse.hbs`,\n39:    and `intake-checklist.md` from the CLI install directory into\n40:    `.super-ralph/` (skips each file if already present).\n41: 3. Creates `.super-ralph/config.toml` from a template, substituting the\n42:    actual `src/index.ts` path of the CLI install.\n43: 4. Creates `.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js` (the `task_complete` tool\n44:    plugin for OpenCode).\n45: 5. Creates `.opencode/package.json` with `@opencode-ai/plugin` dependency.\n46: 6. Spawns `bun install --silent` in `.opencode/` to install plugin\n47:    dependencies.\n48: 7. Creates `tasks/` directory.\n49: 8. Spawns `br init` to initialise the `.beads/` workspace.\n50: 9. Creates or updates the root `AGENTS.md` to include a reference to\n51:    `.super-ralph/AGENTS.md`.\n52: \n53: ## Failure Modes\n54: \n55: | Condition | Behavior | Recovery |\n56: | --- | --- | --- |\n57: | Template file missing from CLI install | Warning logged to console; step skipped | Remaining steps continue |\n58: | Plugin source file missing | Warning logged; plugin file not created | OpenCode plugin will not be available until `init` is re-run after repair |\n59: | `bun install` fails | Error caught and logged as a warning | Remaining steps continue; plugin may not function |\n60: | `br init` fails | Error caught and logged as a warning | Remaining steps continue; `.beads/` workspace may be incomplete |\n61: | File already exists (any step) | Step is skipped silently | Idempotent; no data loss |\n62: \n63: ## Dependencies\n64: \n65: | Dependency | Type | Purpose |\n\n(Showing lines 1-65 of 79. Use offset=66 to continue.)\n</content>","title":"spec/modules/infrastructure/init.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Init\n\n> Scaffolds a new project: creates `.super-ralph/`, copies templates, writes\n> `config.toml`, installs the OpenCode plugin, and runs `br init`.\n\n**Source:** `src/init.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe init module performs one-time project setup for `super-ralph`. It is\nidempotent: running it more than once will skip files that already exist\nrather than overwriting them. The module wires together the three external\ndependencies a project needs: the `.super-ralph/` configuration directory,\nthe OpenCode plugin that provides the `task_complete` tool, and the `.beads/`\nworkspace.\n\n## Triggers\n\n- `runInit(projectDir)` — called by `src/index.ts` when the user runs\n  `super-ralph init`. (`src/index.ts:cmdInit`)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772180622115,"end":1772180622121}}}}
