{"type":"text","timestamp":1772180628199,"sessionID":"ses_361d75adcffeCdUmEUSP3DCUv6","part":{"id":"prt_c9e324fd3002ouzTL4nSiApQAr","sessionID":"ses_361d75adcffeCdUmEUSP3DCUv6","messageID":"msg_c9e324b92001P0x2XFPmDBnxt8","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the issues. The `Vale.Terms` rule for `opencode` is case-sensitive and requires lowercase even in prose. Similarly for `bead`/`beads`. The `Config` title in config.md needs to be `config`. Let me fix all files systematically. I'll do the replacements in prose (non-code) sections:\n\nThe Vale Terms rule is treating these as brand/product name consistency enforcements. I need to:\n1. `OpenCode` in prose → `opencode` \n2. `Bead` (standalone noun referring to the concept) in prose → `bead`\n3. `Beads` (standalone noun) in prose → `beads`\n4. Module title `# Config` → `# config`\n5. `Idempotent` → `idempotent` (in the failure modes table)\n\nLet me fix these one by one:","time":{"start":1772180628195,"end":1772180628195}}}
