========================\n--- /Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/README.md\n+++ /Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/README.md\n@@ -20,13 +20,13 @@\n Specifications cover the following layers:\n \n - **Engine** — The core Ralph loop (select, prompt, execute, evaluate).\n - **Phases** — Reverse, decompose, and forward phase orchestration.\n-- **Subsystems** — Configuration loading, bead integration, OpenCode SDK\n+- **Subsystems** — Configuration loading, bead integration, opencode SDK\n   adapter, template resolution, run-state persistence, and output parsing.\n - **CLI** — Command-line interface surface and option handling.\n \n-Out of scope: internal OpenCode SDK implementation, beads-rust internals, and\n+Out of scope: internal opencode SDK implementation, beads-rust internals, and\n third-party tooling not imported by this project.\n \n ## Navigation\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/README.md","before":"# Spec Directory\n\nThis directory contains reverse-engineered specifications for the super-ralph\nagent framework. All documents are produced by reading observable behavior,\nsource code, and runtime artifacts — not from internal design documents or\nauthor interviews.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `spec/` tree provides a clean-room description of how super-ralph works so\nthat:\n\n- Contributors can understand module contracts without reading all source code.\n- The forward phase can use these docs as authoritative context when\n  implementing beads.\n- Reviewers have a stable reference for verifying that behavior matches intent.\n\n## Scope\n\nSpecifications cover the following layers:\n\n- **Engine** — The core Ralph loop (select, prompt, execute, evaluate).\n- **Phases** — Reverse, decompose, and forward phase orchestration.\n- **Subsystems** — Configuration loading, bead integration, OpenCode SDK\n  adapter, template resolution, run-state persistence, and output parsing.\n- **CLI** — Command-line interface surface and option handling.\n\nOut of scope: internal OpenCode SDK implementation, beads-rust internals, and\nthird-party tooling not imported by this project.\n\n## Navigation\n\nRead documents in this order for a top-down understanding:\n\n1. [CONVENTIONS.md](CONVENTIONS.md) — Writing rules, clean-room constraints,\n   confidence labels, and the module doc template.\n2. Module specs (listed below) — One file per major source module.\n\n## Artifact Table\n\n| Artifact | Path | Status | Covers |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Writing conventions | [CONVENTIONS.md](CONVENTIONS.md) | stable | Meta |\n| Engine loop | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/engine.ts` |\n| Forward phase | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/forward.ts` |\n| Reverse phase | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/reverse.ts` |\n| Decompose phase | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/decompose.ts` |\n| Config loading | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/config.ts` |\n| Bead integration | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/beads.ts` |\n| OpenCode adapter | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/opencode.ts` |\n| Template resolution | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/template.ts` |\n| Run-state persistence | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/run-state.ts` |\n| Output parsing | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/output-parser.ts` |\n| CLI entry point | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/index.ts` |\n\n_Status values: `stable` | `draft` | `pending` | `superseded`_\n\n## Adding a New Spec\n\n1. Copy the module doc template from [CONVENTIONS.md](CONVENTIONS.md).\n2. Name the file `spec/<module-name>.md`.\n3. Add a row to the Artifact Table above.\n4. Follow all clean-room rules in [CONVENTIONS.md](CONVENTIONS.md).\n","after":"# Spec Directory\n\nThis directory contains reverse-engineered specifications for the super-ralph\nagent framework. All documents are produced by reading observable behavior,\nsource code, and runtime artifacts — not from internal design documents or\nauthor interviews.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `spec/` tree provides a clean-room description of how super-ralph works so\nthat:\n\n- Contributors can understand module contracts without reading all source code.\n- The forward phase can use these docs as authoritative context when\n  implementing beads.\n- Reviewers have a stable reference for verifying that behavior matches intent.\n\n## Scope\n\nSpecifications cover the following layers:\n\n- **Engine** — The core Ralph loop (select, prompt, execute, evaluate).\n- **Phases** — Reverse, decompose, and forward phase orchestration.\n- **Subsystems** — Configuration loading, bead integration, opencode SDK\n  adapter, template resolution, run-state persistence, and output parsing.\n- **CLI** — Command-line interface surface and option handling.\n\nOut of scope: internal opencode SDK implementation, beads-rust internals, and\nthird-party tooling not imported by this project.\n\n## Navigation\n\nRead documents in this order for a top-down understanding:\n\n1. [CONVENTIONS.md](CONVENTIONS.md) — Writing rules, clean-room constraints,\n   confidence labels, and the module doc template.\n2. Module specs (listed below) — One file per major source module.\n\n## Artifact Table\n\n| Artifact | Path | Status | Covers |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Writing conventions | [CONVENTIONS.md](CONVENTIONS.md) | stable | Meta |\n| Engine loop | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/engine.ts` |\n| Forward phase | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/forward.ts` |\n| Reverse phase | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/reverse.ts` |\n| Decompose phase | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/decompose.ts` |\n| Config loading | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/config.ts` |\n| Bead integration | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/beads.ts` |\n| OpenCode adapter | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/opencode.ts` |\n| Template resolution | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/template.ts` |\n| Run-state persistence | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/run-state.ts` |\n| Output parsing | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/output-parser.ts` |\n| CLI entry point | _(pending)_ | draft | `src/index.ts` |\n\n_Status values: `stable` | `draft` | `pending` | `superseded`_\n\n## Adding a New Spec\n\n1. Copy the module doc template from [CONVENTIONS.md](CONVENTIONS.md).\n2. Name the file `spec/<module-name>.md`.\n3. Add a row to the Artifact Table above.\n4. Follow all clean-room rules in [CONVENTIONS.md](CONVENTIONS.md).\n","additions":2,"deletions":2},"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772180699239,"end":1772180699262}}}}
