        "result": "task_id: ses_361d70de2ffenybq0c8kKhyBL0 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a comprehensive summary of every module in `src/`:\n\n---\n\n## `src/types.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Pure type definitions — no runtime logic. Defines the shared data model for the entire framework.\n\n**Exported types:**\n- `BeadInfo` — a task/work item from the `br` CLI: `{ id, title, description?, status, labels, priority, dependsOn, blocks, type?, parentId }`\n- `LoopConfig` — full config structure loaded from `.super-ralph/config.toml`, with sub-objects: `engine`, `opencode`, `cli`, `models`, `modelsAreas`, `reverse`, `decompose`\n- `IterationResult` — result of one agent loop iteration: `{ iteration, beadId, beadTitle, status, reason?, model, duration, cost?, tokens?, filesChanged?, transcriptPath? }`\n- `CompletionResult` — what an OpenCode session signals at the end: `{ status, reason? }`. Status is one of: `\"complete\" | \"phase_done\" | \"blocked\" | \"failed\" | \"stalled\" | \"timeout\" | \"error\"`\n- `LoopResult` — aggregate result of a full phase run: `{ completed, failed, skipped, totalTime, maxIterations, iterations[] }`\n- `PhaseFlags` — base CLI flags: `{ dryRun, maxIterations?, modelOverride?, attach? }`\n- `ForwardFlags extends PhaseFlags` — adds `epicId`\n- `DecomposeFlags extends PhaseFlags` — adds `specPath`, `epicTitle?`\n- `ReverseFlags extends PhaseFlags` — adds `inputs[]`, `outputDir?`, `skill?`, `interactive?`, `answersFile?`\n- `ErrorStrategy` — `\"retry\" | \"skip\" | \"abort\"`\n\n**Dependencies:** None.\n\n---\n\n## `src/config.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Loads and merges the project TOML configuration, and resolves which AI model to use for a given bead.\n\n**Exported functions:**\n- `loadConfig(projectDir: string): LoopConfig` — reads `.super-ralph/config.toml`, deep-merges with hard-coded defaults. Returns defaults if file missing.\n- `resolveModel(beadLabels: string[], beadTitle: string, config: LoopConfig, cliOverride?: string): { providerID: string; modelID: string }` — model selection with three priority tiers: (1) CLI `--model` override, (2) bead `area:*` label mapped via `config.modelsAreas`, (3) `config.models.default`.\n\n**Notable constants (defaults):**\n```\ntimeout_minutes: 30\ninactivity_timeout_seconds: 180\niteration_delay_ms: 2000\nstrategy: \"retry\"\nmax_retries: 3\nopencode.url: \"http://localhost:4096\"\nmodels.default: \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\nreverse.output_dir: \"docs/specs\"\ndecompose.include_review/bugscan/audit: true\n```\n\n**Inputs:** Project directory path, optionally a `cliOverride` model string in `\"provider/model\"` format.\n**Outputs:** `LoopConfig` object or `{ providerID, modelID }` tuple.\n\n**Side effects:** Reads file from disk (sync). Throws if model string is not in `\"provider/model\"` format.\n\n**External dependencies:** `fs` (node), `path` (node), `@iarna/toml` (npm).\n**Internal dependencies:** `./types.js`\n\n---\n\n## `src/beads.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Thin wrapper around the `br` CLI (the Beads Rust task manager). All bead operations spawn `br` as a subprocess and parse its JSON output.\n\n**Exported functions:**\n- `runBr(args: string[], cwd?: string): Promise<unknown>` — general-purpose `br` subprocess runner. Filters log lines, finds JSON start, parses.\n- `getAllReady(epicId: string): Promise<BeadInfo[]>` — calls `br ready --parent <id> --json --sort hybrid`. Returns unblocked beads sorted by hybrid priority.\n- `getBeadDetails(beadId: string): Promise<BeadInfo>` — calls `br show <id> --json`. Returns a single bead.\n- `closeBead(beadId: string, reason?: string): Promise<{ suggestNext: BeadInfo[] }>` — calls `br close <id> --suggest-next --json`. Returns newly unblocked beads.\n- `getAllBeads(epicId: string): Promise<BeadInfo[]>` — gets epic children via `br show`, then fetches each child's details via `br list --all --json --id ...`.\n- `getEpicProgress(epicId: string): Promise<{ total, completed, remaining }>` — counts beads by status.\n\n**Side effects:** Spawns `br` subprocess for each call. Throws `Error` on non-zero exit codes with stderr included.\n\n**Error behavior:** Throws with message `\"br <args> failed (exit N): <stderr>\"` if `br` exits non-zero. Empty results (no ready beads) return `[]`.\n\n**External dependencies:** `Bun.spawn` (Bun runtime). No npm packages.\n**Internal dependencies:** `./types.js`\n\n---\n\n## `src/template.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Loads Handlebars (`.hbs`) prompt templates from the project's `.super-ralph/` directory and renders them with variable substitution.\n\n**Exported functions:**\n- `loadTemplate(projectDir: string, filename?: string): HandlebarsTemplateDelegate` — reads and compiles `.super-ralph/<filename>`. Defaults to `\"forward.hbs\"`. Throws if template not found.\n- `renderPrompt(template: HandlebarsTemplateDelegate, vars: Record<string, unknown>): string` — renders the template with provided variables.\n\n**Side effects:** Reads file from disk (sync). Throws if template file is missing with a hint to run `super-ralph init`.\n\n**External dependencies:** `handlebars` (npm), `fs` (node), `path` (node).\n\n---\n\n## `src/skills.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Resolves \"skill\" files (question banks / domain-specific prompts) for the reverse phase, and provides the CLI install directory path.\n\n**Exported functions:**\n- `loadSkill(skillNameOrPath: string | undefined, cliDir: string): string | null` — resolves built-in skill names (`feature`, `bug`, `hotfix`, `refactor`) to `skills/<name>.md` in the CLI install, or resolves arbitrary file paths. Returns file content as string, or `null` if no skill given.\n- `getCliDir(): string` — returns the directory where the `super-ralph` CLI is installed, by resolving `import.meta.url` up one level from `src/`.\n\n**Notable constants:** `BUILT_IN_SKILLS = [\"feature\", \"bug\", \"hotfix\", \"refactor\"]`\n\n**Error behavior:** Throws if a named built-in skill file doesn't exist, or if an explicit file path doesn't exist.\n\n**External dependencies:** `fs` (node), `path` (node).\n\n---\n\n## `src/timeout.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Utility that races a promise against a deadline timer.\n\n**Exported functions:**\n- `withTimeout<T>(task: Promise<T>, timeoutMs: number, errorMessage: string): Promise<T>` — returns the task result if it resolves before the deadline, otherwise rejects with `new Error(errorMessage)`. Always clears the timer in `finally`.\n\n**Side effects:** None. Pure async utility.\n\n**External dependencies:** None.\n\n---\n\n## `src/output-parser.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Captures and formats two parallel output streams from an OpenCode session: the raw JSON event stream and the human-readable display text. Enforces a 250,000-character size limit on each, prepending a truncation marker when exceeded.\n\n**Exported class:**\n- `StreamCapture` — stateful capture buffer with methods:\n  - `addRawLine(line: string): void` — appends a raw JSON event line\n  - `addDisplayText(text: string): void` — appends rendered text\n  - `toolStatusText(toolName, status, error?): string` — formats a tool call status line (e.g., `\"[tool: bash] \"`, `\"done\\n\"`, `\"error: ...\\n\"`)\n  - `getRawOutput(): string`\n  - `getDisplayOutput(): string`\n\n**Notable constants:** `MAX_STREAM_CAPTURE_CHARS = 250_000`\n\n**Side effects:** None. Pure in-memory state.\n\n**External dependencies:** None.\n\n---\n\n## `src/events.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Typed event system for the engine loop. Defines all possible engine lifecycle events and provides an emitter with listener management plus a default console renderer.\n\n**Exported types:**\n- `EngineEvent` — discriminated union of 12 event types covering the full loop lifecycle: `loop.description`, `loop.dry_run_iteration`, `loop.dry_run_complete`, `server.started`, `server.attached`, `server.attach_hint`, `iteration.started`, `iteration.session_created`, `iteration.completed`, `iteration.blocked`, `iteration.retrying`, `iteration.failed`, `iteration.error`, `loop.completed`\n- `EngineEventListener` — `(event: EngineEvent) => void`\n\n**Exported class:**\n- `EngineEventEmitter` — simple pub/sub with `on(listener): () => void` (returns unsubscribe fn) and `emit(event): void`\n\n**Exported function:**\n- `attachDefaultConsoleRenderer(emitter): () => void` — registers a listener that prints formatted console output for all event types. Returns a detach function.\n\n**Side effects:** `console.log` / `console.error` calls in the default renderer.\n\n**Internal dependencies:** `./types.js`\n\n---\n\n## `src/run-state.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Creates and manages a run artifact directory for each engine run. Writes structured state files that can be queried with `super-ralph status`.\n\n**Exported interface:** `RunTracker` — `{ runId, runDir, recordEvent(event), writeIterationTranscript(iteration, label, rawOutput?, displayOutput?): string | undefined, finalize(status) }`\n\n**Exported function:**\n- `startRunTracker(projectDir, description, maxIterations): RunTracker` — creates `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/` directory tree with `session.json`, `events.jsonl`, and `iterations/` subdirectory. Also writes a global `.super-ralph/session.json` (latest run pointer).\n\n**Run ID format:** `\"<timestamp>-<random6chars>\"`\n\n**Side effects (extensive file writes):**\n- Creates `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/` and `iterations/` dirs\n- Writes `session.json` (JSON state) after every event\n- Writes `.super-ralph/session.json` (global latest pointer) after every event\n- Appends to `events.jsonl` (JSONL) for each event\n- Writes per-iteration `iterations/<NNN>-<label>.log` transcripts\n\n**Internal dependencies:** `./events.js`\n**External dependencies:** `fs` (node), `path` (node).\n\n---\n\n## `src/run-status.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Read-only inspection of run artifacts written by `run-state.ts`. Used by `super-ralph status --run`.\n\n**Exported interfaces:**\n- `RunSessionStatus` — shape of `session.json`: `{ runId, status, description, maxIterations, startedAt, updatedAt, currentIteration, completed, failed, skipped }`\n- `RunStatus` — full status view: `{ runId, runDir, session, eventCount, lastEventType?, lastEventTimestamp?, latestTranscript? }`\n\n**Exported function:**\n- `getRunStatus(projectDir: string, runRef: string): RunStatus` — resolves `runRef` (either a specific run ID or `\"latest\"`) by scanning `.super-ralph/runs/`. Reads `session.json`, counts lines in `events.jsonl`, finds most recent transcript file.\n\n**Error behavior:** Throws descriptive errors if no runs directory exists, run ID not found, or `session.json` is missing.\n\n**Side effects:** Read-only file system access (sync).\n\n**External dependencies:** `fs` (node), `path` (node).\n\n---\n\n## `src/progress.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Maintains a human-readable Markdown progress log at `.super-ralph/progress.md`, recording each iteration's outcome. Also provides a reader for injecting recent history into prompts.\n\n**Exported functions:**\n- `readRecentProgress(projectDir, count?: number): string` — reads the last N iteration blocks from `progress.md`. Splits on `## Iteration N` headers.\n- `appendProgress(projectDir, iteration, result: IterationResult): void` — appends a formatted Markdown block for the given iteration.\n- `formatProgressEntry(iteration, result): string` — formats a single iteration block with model, duration, cost, tokens, files changed, transcript path, and reason.\n\n**Side effects:** Reads and writes `.super-ralph/progress.md` (creates if missing).\n\n**External dependencies:** `fs` (node), `path` (node).\n**Internal dependencies:** `./types.js`\n\n---\n\n## `src/opencode.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Manages the OpenCode AI coding agent server lifecycle and session orchestration. This is the core AI execution layer — it spawns or attaches to an OpenCode server, creates sessions, sends prompts, and streams SSE event output back in real time.\n\n**Exported interfaces:**\n- `PromptResult` — `{ completion: CompletionResult, cost, tokens, filesChanged, rawOutput, displayOutput }`\n- `ServerHandle` — `{ client: OpencodeClient, url: string, close: () => void }`\n\n**Exported functions:**\n- `checkBrokenSymlinks(opts?: { fix? }): string[]` — scans `~/.config/opencode/plugins/` and `commands/` for broken symlinks. Returns broken paths; optionally removes them (`fix: true`).\n- `startServer(): Promise<ServerHandle>` — starts an ephemeral OpenCode server on port 0 (OS-assigned), fixes broken symlinks first, verifies server is responsive.\n- `connectToServer(url): Promise<ServerHandle>` — attaches to an existing OpenCode server. `close()` is a no-op.\n- `createSession(client, title): Promise<string>` — creates a named session, returns session ID.\n- `runPrompt(client, sessionId, prompt, model, systemPrompt?, serverUrl?, inactivityTimeoutMs?): Promise<PromptResult>` — sends a prompt via `promptAsync()`, subscribes to SSE events, streams text deltas to stdout in real time, extracts `task_complete` tool call result, sums cost/tokens, collects file diffs.\n- `showToast(client, message, variant): Promise<void>` — shows a TUI notification; falls back to console.log.\n- `abortSession(client, sessionId): Promise<void>` — aborts a running session.\n\n**Side effects:**\n- Spawns OpenCode server process (via `createOpencode`)\n- SSE network connections to OpenCode server\n- `process.stdout.write` for real-time streaming output\n- `process.stderr.write` for debug output when `SUPER_RALPH_DEBUG` env var is set\n- Reads/removes files in `~/.config/opencode/`\n- Best-effort `session.abort()` on inactivity timeout\n\n**Error behavior:** Throws on server startup failure, unreachable server, inactivity timeout (`Session inactive for Ns`).\n\n**Notable env var:** `SUPER_RALPH_DEBUG` — enables verbose event logging to stderr.\n\n**External dependencies:** `@opencode-ai/sdk` (npm, v1 client), `@opencode-ai/sdk/v2` (npm, v2 client), `fs`, `path`, `os` (node).\n**Internal dependencies:** `./types.js`, `./output-parser.js`\n\n---\n\n## `src/interactive.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Handles interactive OpenCode sessions where the AI agent asks the human user questions via a terminal UI. Uses `@clack/prompts` to render select/multiselect/text prompts. Also supports mock/pre-recorded answers for automated testing.\n\n**Exported types:**\n- `InteractiveClient` (re-export of `OpencodeClient` from v2 SDK)\n- `InteractiveResult` — `{ completion, cost, tokens, filesChanged, rawOutput, displayOutput }`\n- `MockAnswer` — `{ match: string, answer: string | number }` — for test fixtures\n\n**Exported functions:**\n- `createInteractiveClient(baseUrl): OpencodeClient` — creates a v2 SDK client.\n- `runInteractiveSession(client, sessionId, prompt, model, systemPrompt?, inactivityTimeoutMs?): Promise<InteractiveResult>` — runs an interactive session. Subscribes to SSE events, handles `question.asked` by prompting the user (or using mock answers), handles `session.idle` / `session.error`, streams text deltas to stdout. Returns gathered results.\n- `loadMockAnswers(filePath): void` — loads mock answers from JSON file (for non-interactive testing).\n- `clearMockAnswers(): void` — resets mock answer state.\n- `hasMockAnswersLoaded(): boolean`\n- `getMockAnswerLog(): Array<{ question, answer }>` — returns log of Q&A during mock session.\n\n**Mock answer matching:** Matches by case-insensitive substring against the question text. If numeric, selects that option index. If `\"first\"`, selects option 0. Unmatched defaults to option 0.\n\n**Side effects:**\n- `process.stdout.write` for streaming text output\n- Terminal prompts via `@clack/prompts` (stdin/stdout interaction)\n- Best-effort `session.abort()` on inactivity timeout\n- Module-level mutable state (`mockAnswers`, `mockAnswerLog`) — singleton pattern\n\n**External dependencies:** `@opencode-ai/sdk/v2` (npm), `@clack/prompts` (npm), `fs` (node).\n**Internal dependencies:** `./types.js`, `./output-parser.js`\n\n---\n\n## `src/engine.ts`\n\n**What it does:** The core loop orchestrator. Implements the generic `runPhaseLoop` function that all three phases (forward, decompose, reverse) use. Manages the iteration lifecycle: server startup, prompt dispatch, result handling, retry/abort/skip strategy, event emission, progress logging, and run artifact tracking.\n\n**Exported interfaces:**\n- `PhaseIteration` — `{ prompt, model, sessionTitle, iterationLabel, beadId?, systemPrompt? }`\n- `PhaseCallbacks` — callback interface phases must implement: `{ setup(config, dryRun): Promise<{ maxIterations, description }>, nextIteration(config, iteration): Promise<PhaseIteration | null>, handleResult(result, iteration): Promise<boolean> }`\n\n**Exported function:**\n- `runPhaseLoop(projectDir, callbacks, flags, onEvent?): Promise<LoopResult>`\n\n**Loop behavior:**\n1. Loads config, calls `setup()`, starts `RunTracker`\n2. In dry-run mode: iterates `nextIteration()` without running AI, emits dry-run events, returns immediately\n3. Starts or attaches to OpenCode server\n4. Loop up to `maxIterations`:\n   - Calls `nextIteration()` — `null` return exits loop\n   - Creates OpenCode session, runs prompt with `withTimeout()` (wall-clock timeout)\n   - Writes iteration transcript via `RunTracker`\n   - Appends to `progress.md`\n   - Calls `handleResult()` — `false` return exits loop\n   - On `complete`/`phase_done`: increments completed counter\n   - On `blocked`: increments skipped\n   - On failure + `retry` strategy: decrements iteration counter (retries same bead)\n   - On failure + `abort` strategy: breaks loop\n   - On failure + `skip` (default): increments failed, continues\n   - Applies `iteration_delay_ms` between iterations\n5. Finalizes `RunTracker`, cleans up server and event listeners\n\n**Side effects:**\n- Spawns/connects to OpenCode server\n- File writes via `RunTracker` and `appendProgress`\n- Console output via event emitter\n- Configurable `iteration_delay_ms` sleep between iterations\n\n**Internal dependencies:** `./config.js`, `./opencode.js`, `./progress.js`, `./types.js`, `./events.js`, `./run-state.js`, `./timeout.js`\n\n---\n\n## `src/forward.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Implements the **Forward phase** — the \"beads → code\" loop. Picks the highest-priority ready bead from an epic, instructs the AI to implement it, and loops until no ready beads remain.\n\n**Exported function:**\n- `runForward(projectDir, flags: ForwardFlags): Promise<LoopResult>`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- `setup`: fetches all beads to determine `maxIterations = beads.length * 2`\n- `nextIteration`: calls `getAllReady()`, picks `readyBeads[0]` (highest priority), gets bead details, reads recent progress, resolves model by bead labels/area, renders `forward.hbs` prompt\n- `handleResult`: stops on `phase_done`, continues on `complete` or any other status\n\n**System prompt injected:** Tells agent to implement the bead, run typecheck, close with `br close`, and always call `task_complete`.\n\n**Side effects:** Reads bead data from `br` CLI, reads `progress.md`, renders Handlebars template.\n\n**Internal dependencies:** `./engine.js`, `./beads.js`, `./template.js`, `./progress.js`, `./config.js`, `./types.js`\n\n---\n\n## `src/decompose.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Implements the **Decompose phase** — the \"spec → beads\" loop. Reads a spec file and instructs the AI to iteratively create beads in an epic until the spec is fully covered.\n\n**Exported function:**\n- `runDecompose(projectDir, flags: DecomposeFlags): Promise<LoopResult>`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- `setup`: loads `decompose.hbs` template, validates spec file exists. In real mode, creates the epic with `br create --type epic`. Sets `maxIterations = 50`.\n- `nextIteration`: reads spec content, fetches existing beads, renders template with `includeReview/Bugscan/Audit` flags from config\n- `handleResult`: stops on `phase_done`, continues on `complete`\n\n**System prompt injected:** Tells agent to create small verifiable beads using `br create`, call `task_complete` with `phase_done` when spec is fully covered.\n\n**Side effects:** Creates an epic via `br create` on startup (unless dry-run). Reads spec file each iteration.\n\n**Internal dependencies:** `./engine.js`, `./template.js`, `./config.js`, `./beads.js`, `./types.js`\n**External dependencies:** `fs` (node)\n\n---\n\n## `src/reverse.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Implements the **Reverse phase** — converts inputs (files, URLs, descriptions) into a spec document. Supports two sub-modes: **interactive** (AI asks user questions via terminal) and **autonomous** (AI reads inputs and writes spec iteratively).\n\n**Exported function:**\n- `runReverse(projectDir, flags: ReverseFlags): Promise<LoopResult>` — dispatches to `runInteractive` or `runAutonomous` based on `flags.interactive`\n\n**Interactive mode (`runInteractive`):**\n- Creates a v2 OpenCode session directly (bypassing `runPhaseLoop`)\n- Loads skill content, renders `reverse.hbs` prompt\n- Calls `runInteractiveSession()` — user answers AI questions via clack prompts\n- Supports mock answers file for automated testing\n- Wrapped with `withTimeout()`, best-effort abort on timeout\n- Writes transcript via `RunTracker`\n- Returns `completed=1` on `phase_done`, `skipped=1` on `blocked`, `failed=1` otherwise\n\n**Autonomous mode (`runAutonomous`):**\n- Uses `runPhaseLoop` with `maxIterations = 20`\n- Each iteration: finds most recently modified `.md` file in `outputDir`, renders prompt with current spec content\n- Stops on `phase_done`, continues on `complete`\n\n**System prompt injected:** Tells agent to describe WHAT/WHY not HOW, use question tool, save spec, call `task_complete`.\n\n**Side effects:**\n- Creates output directory (`docs/specs` by default)\n- Reads/writes spec `.md` files\n- Spawns/connects to OpenCode server\n- Terminal UI interaction (interactive mode)\n\n**Internal dependencies:** `./engine.js`, `./template.js`, `./config.js`, `./opencode.js`, `./interactive.js`, `./skills.js`, `./types.js`, `./run-state.js`, `./timeout.js`\n**External dependencies:** `fs`, `path` (node)\n\n---\n\n## `src/init.ts`\n\n**What it does:** Scaffolds a new project for use with `super-ralph`. Run via `super-ralph init`.\n\n**Exported function:**\n- `runInit(projectDir: string): Promise<void>`\n\n**Actions performed (in order), all idempotent:**\n1. Creates `.super-ralph/` directory\n2. Copies template files from CLI install: `AGENTS.md`, `forward.hbs`, `decompose.hbs`, `reverse.hbs`, `intake-checklist.md` (skips if already present)\n3. Creates `.super-ralph/config.toml` from template, substituting the actual CLI `src/index.ts` path into `cli.path`\n4. Creates `.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js` (provides the `task_complete` tool to OpenCode), creates `.opencode/package.json` with `@opencode-ai/plugin` dependency, runs `bun install --silent` in `.opencode/`\n5. Creates `tasks/` directory (legacy compatibility)\n6. Runs `br init` to initialize `.beads/` workspace\n7. Creates or updates root `AGENTS.md` to reference `.super-ralph/AGENTS.md`\n\n**Side effects:** Creates/copies files, spawns `bun install` and `br init` subprocesses.\n\n**Error behavior:** Warnings (not throws) if template files or plugin source are missing. `bun install` and `br init` failures are caught and reported as warnings.\n\n**Internal dependencies:** `./skills.js`\n**External dependencies:** `fs`, `path` (node), `Bun.spawn`\n\n---\n\n## `src/index.ts`\n\n**What it does:** The CLI entry point (`#!/usr/bin/env bun`). Parses `process.argv`, dispatches to subcommands, and handles process exit codes.\n\n**Commands implemented:**\n| Command | Handler | Description |\n|---------|---------|-------------|\n| `forward` (alias: `run`) | `cmdForward` | Runs the Forward phase |\n| `decompose` | `cmdDecompose` | Runs the Decompose phase |\n| `reverse` | `cmdReverse` | Runs the Reverse phase |\n| `init` | `runInit` | Scaffolds project |\n| `status` | `cmdStatus` | Shows epic bead progress or run artifact status |\n| `doctor` | `cmdDoctor` | Preflight checks |\n| `help` / `--help` / `-h` | `printUsage` | Shows usage text |\n\n**Argument parser (`parseArgs`):**\n- Boolean flags (never take a value): `--dry-run`, `--interactive`, `--fix`\n- All other `--flag value` pairs consume the next argument as value\n- Positional arguments collected separately\n\n**`cmdDoctor` checks:** bun installation, `br` CLI, `.super-ralph/AGENTS.md`, all three `.hbs` templates, `config.toml`, `.beads/` workspace, `cli.path` in config, broken symlinks in `~/.config/opencode/` (with optional `--fix` to remove them).\n\n**Side effects:**\n- `process.exit(1)` on error or if `result.failed > 0`\n- `writeFileSync` for `--json <path>` output\n- All the side effects of the subcommands it calls\n\n**Internal dependencies:** `./forward.js`, `./decompose.js`, `./reverse.js`, `./init.js`, `./beads.js`, `./config.js`, `./opencode.js`, `./run-status.js`, `./types.js`\n**External dependencies:** `fs`, `path` (node), `Bun.spawn`\n\n---\n\n## Cross-Cutting Architecture Summary\n\nThe three \"phase\" modules (`forward`, `decompose`, `reverse`) all implement the `PhaseCallbacks` interface and delegate to `runPhaseLoop` in `engine.ts`, which is the single orchestration core. The data flow is:\n\n```\nindex.ts (CLI)\n  └── forward/decompose/reverse.ts (phase logic)\n        └── engine.ts (loop orchestration)\n              ├── opencode.ts (AI session management)\n              │     └── output-parser.ts (stream capture)\n              ├── events.ts (typed event bus)\n              ├── run-state.ts (artifact persistence)\n              ├── progress.ts (progress.md append log)\n              └── timeout.ts (deadline wrapper)\n        ├── beads.ts (br CLI wrapper)\n        ├── template.ts (Handlebars rendering)\n        ├── config.ts (TOML config + model resolution)\n        └── skills.ts (skill file loading)\n```\n\nThe `interactive.ts` module is a parallel session path used only by `reverse.ts` in interactive mode — it bypasses `runPhaseLoop` and runs a single OpenCode session with real-time terminal question answering.\n</task_result>"
